-use clean architecture software development approach when designing the system (domain,usecases and infrastruture)
-always follow clean code coding best practices when developing
-write testable maintainable and readable code
-Every function, variable, and parameter must have explicit types.
-Use DTOs (Data Transfer Objects) for communication between layers.
-adhere to Single Responsibility Principle when declaring each module/class/function
-follow pascalCase when declaring entities
-follow camelCase when declaring functions and variables
-for interfaces declaration use 'I' prefix (e.g., ICustomerAccountRepository)
-for DTO declarations use 'DTO' suffix (e.g., CreateCustomerAccountDTO)
-maintain 80% unit test coverage including functions and all other testable lines
-run and check for eslint violations and correct them
-always maintain pure functions in domain layer
-check on type safety
-add TSDOCS to each function declaration for professional, maintainable, and team-friendly code 